` Very bad ' conditions in Haiti 's hospitals The Red Cross has warned hospitals in Haiti 's capital are struggling in the earthquake aftermath because of a lack of doctors and equipment .
Ricardo Condi , the head of the charity in Port - au - Prince , said '' the needs are huge '' and conditions are '' very bad '' .
